<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBFCCDFEABFCD2" bold="true" box="[189,348,796,822]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Valid species</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBFC9DFBF9FC16" blockId="6.[189,1399,843,1010]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBFC9DFDB5FC81" authority="(Castro et al., 2006)" authorityName="Leduc &amp; Verschelde" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Castro et al." baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[189,578,843,869]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="elongata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBFC9DFEB3FC81" box="[189,324,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. elongata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153820FC9AFDCDFC81" author="Castro F. J. V. &amp; Bezerra T. N. C. &amp; Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[342,570,843,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref10284" refString="Castro F. J. V., Bezerra T. N. C., Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2006. Spirinia elongata, sp. nov. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from Pina Basin, Pernambuco, Brazil. Zootaxa 1121: 53 - 68." type="journal article" year="2006">
Castro 
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1538D8FC9DFE1BFC81" box="[430,492,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0DFFA27BFFC20B153B3AFC9AFD26FC81" box="[588,721,843,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(synonym: 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B153A15FC9DFAD5FC81" authority="Castro et al., 2006" authorityName="Castro" authorityYear="2006" box="[867,1314,843,870]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Spirinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153A15FC9DFBC5FC81" box="[867,1074,843,870]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spirinia elongata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153D4AFC9AFAD5FC81" author="Castro F. J. V. &amp; Bezerra T. N. C. &amp; Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[1084,1314,843,869]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref10284" refString="Castro F. J. V., Bezerra T. N. C., Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2006. Spirinia elongata, sp. nov. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from Pina Basin, Pernambuco, Brazil. Zootaxa 1121: 53 - 68." type="journal article" year="2006">
Castro 
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153DE5FC9DFB26FC81" box="[1171,1233,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, 2006
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Main diagnostic characters: “...one very small subventral tooth and two small dorsal teeth.” The drawings show amphids completely surrounded by body annulations, but the authors describe a conico-cylindrical tail with annuli which are more evident in the tail region compared to those along the rest of the body; thus, we transfer this species to 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B153B45FC08FD55FC16" authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[563,674,985,1010]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153B45FC08FD55FC16" box="[563,674,985,1010]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153BC7FC09FC7FFC16" author="Castro F. J. V. &amp; Bezerra T. N. C. &amp; Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[689,904,984,1010]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="53 - 68" refId="ref10284" refString="Castro F. J. V., Bezerra T. N. C., Da Silva M. C. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2006. Spirinia elongata, sp. nov. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from Pina Basin, Pernambuco, Brazil. Zootaxa 1121: 53 - 68." type="journal article" year="2006">
Castro 
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153A71FC08FCB5FC16" box="[775,834,984,1010]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 3c, 4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBFBCAFADCFBB2" blockId="6.[189,1398,1049,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBFBCAFE06FBD7" authority="Vitiello, 1971" authorityName="Vitiello" authorityYear="1971" box="[189,497,1049,1076]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="flagellata">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBFBCAFEB0FBD7" box="[189,327,1049,1076]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. flagellata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B15383BFBC8FE06FBD7" author="Vitiello P." box="[333,497,1049,1075]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="647 - 690" refId="ref11590" refString="Vitiello P. 1971. Nematodes libres marins des vases profondes du Golfe du Lion III. Monhysterida, Araeolaimida, Desmodorida. Tethys 2: 647 - 690." type="journal article" year="1971">Vitiello, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Main diagnostic characters: “Amphid situated anterior to cuticle striations or partially surrounded by them”; very long and slender, almost filiform tail (
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153D55FBEDFB34FBB2" author="Vitiello P." box="[1059,1219,1084,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="647 - 690" refId="ref11590" refString="Vitiello P. 1971. Nematodes libres marins des vases profondes du Golfe du Lion III. Monhysterida, Araeolaimida, Desmodorida. Tethys 2: 647 - 690." type="journal article" year="1971">Vitiello 1971</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 29).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBFBAEFBB8FB5F" blockId="6.[189,1399,1150,1211]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBFBAEFD90FB7C" authority="Wieser &amp; Hopper, 1967" authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[189,615,1150,1176]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBFBAEFEC1FB7C" box="[189,310,1150,1176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. hamata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153836FBAFFD90FB7C" author="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B." box="[320,615,1150,1176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="239 - 343" refId="ref11687" refString="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B. 1967. Marine nematodes of the east coast of North America. I. Florida. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 135: 239 - 343." type="journal article" year="1967">Wieser &amp; Hopper, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Drawing shows amphids only partially located within the body annuli; long and slender, almost filiform tail (
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153BA6FB70FC1FFB5F" author="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B." box="[720,1000,1185,1211]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="239 - 343" refId="ref11687" refString="Wieser W. &amp; Hopper B. 1967. Marine nematodes of the east coast of North America. I. Florida. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 135: 239 - 343." type="journal article" year="1967">Wieser &amp; Hopper 1967</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 18).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBFB35FD6DFA6D" blockId="6.[189,1399,1250,1418]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBFB35FE08FB18" authority="(Silva et al., 2009)" authorityName="Leduc &amp; Verschelde" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Silva et al." baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[189,511,1250,1277]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="lara" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBFB35FEF9FB18" box="[189,270,1250,1277]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. lara</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153857FB33FE01FB18" author="Silva M. C. &amp; Castro F. J. V. &amp; Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[289,502,1250,1277]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref11270" refString="Silva M. C., Castro F. J. V., Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2009. Spirinia lara sp. n. and Spirinia sophia sp. n. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from the Brazilian continental margin (Campos Basin, Rio de Janeiro). Zootaxa 2081: 31 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">
Silva 
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B15381CFB35FE58FB18" box="[362,431,1250,1277]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.,</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0DFFA27BFFC20B153B7CFB33FD78FB18" box="[522,655,1250,1276]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(synonym: 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B153A54FB35FB69FB18" authority="Silva et al., 2009" authorityName="Silva" authorityYear="2009" box="[802,1182,1250,1278]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Spirinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="lara">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153A54FB35FC4BFB18" box="[802,956,1250,1278]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spirinia lara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153AB1FB33FB69FB18" author="Silva M. C. &amp; Castro F. J. V. &amp; Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[967,1182,1250,1277]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref11270" refString="Silva M. C., Castro F. J. V., Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2009. Spirinia lara sp. n. and Spirinia sophia sp. n. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from the Brazilian continental margin (Campos Basin, Rio de Janeiro). Zootaxa 2081: 31 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">
Silva 
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153D78FB35FBBBFB18" box="[1038,1100,1250,1277]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, 2009
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Main diagnostic characters: “Buccal cavity with one dorsal tooth and two minute ventrosublateral teeth” and “Cuticle with transverse striae..., less obvious in head region than in tail.” Drawing shows amphid with annulations to mid-level of amphid only, and tail is described as conico-cylindrical. This species is therefore transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539ADFAA0FEBDFA6E" authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[219,330,1393,1418]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539ADFAA0FEBDFA6E" box="[219,330,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B15382FFABEFDD7FA6D" author="Silva M. C. &amp; Castro F. J. V. &amp; Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V." box="[345,544,1391,1418]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="31 - 45" refId="ref11270" refString="Silva M. C., Castro F. J. V., Cavalcanti M. F. &amp; Fonseca-Genevois V. 2009. Spirinia lara sp. n. and Spirinia sophia sp. n. (Nematoda, Desmodoridae) from the Brazilian continental margin (Campos Basin, Rio de Janeiro). Zootaxa 2081: 31 - 45." type="journal article" year="2009">
Silva 
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1538E9FAA0FE2EFA6D" box="[415,473,1391,1418]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2–3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBFA63FEA3F9F5" blockId="6.[189,1399,1457,1553]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBFA63FD50FA2F" authority="Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989" authorityName="Vincx &amp; Gourbault" authorityYear="1989" box="[189,679,1457,1483]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="megamphida">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBFA63FE86FA2F" box="[189,369,1457,1483]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. megamphida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B15380EFA60FD50FA2F" author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." box="[376,679,1457,1483]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Drawing shows substantial portion of the amphids is located on the non-annulated lip region; conico-cylindrical tail with more prominent annuli (
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153DE2FA05FF0BF9F5" author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault 1989</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBF9EBFBFEF992" blockId="6.[189,1398,1593,1654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBF9EBFE45F9B7" authority="Coles, 1987" authorityName="Coles" authorityYear="1987" box="[189,434,1593,1619]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="mokii">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBF9EBFEECF9B7" box="[189,283,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. mokii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153854F9E8FE45F9B7" author="Coles J. W." box="[290,434,1593,1619]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="79 - 101" refId="ref10455" refString="Coles J. W. 1987. Observations on the marine nematode genus Spirinia Gerlach, 1963 (Desmodoridae: Spiriniinae) with descriptions of two new species. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 53: 79 - 101." type="journal article" year="1987">Coles, 1987</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Main diagnostic character: ‘‘...cuticle appears smooth…’’, hence amphids are not surrounded by annuli; long and slender filiform tail (
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153A53F98DFC47F992" author="Coles J. W." box="[805,944,1628,1654]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="79 - 101" refId="ref10455" refString="Coles J. W. 1987. Observations on the marine nematode genus Spirinia Gerlach, 1963 (Desmodoridae: Spiriniinae) with descriptions of two new species. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History (Zoology) 53: 79 - 101." type="journal article" year="1987">Coles 1987</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 5).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBF94EFE06F91A" blockId="6.[189,1399,1693,1790]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBF94EFD73F953" authority="Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989" authorityName="Vincx &amp; Gourbault" authorityYear="1989" box="[189,644,1693,1720]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="papillata">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBF94EFEB1F953" box="[189,326,1693,1720]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. papillata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153839F94CFD73F953" author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." box="[335,644,1693,1719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault, 1989</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Drawing shows anterior half of amphids on non-annulated lip region and posterior half located within the annulated head region; long, conico-cylindrical tail (
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153C59F911FE6FF91A" author="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="103 - 114" refId="ref11553" refString="Vincx M. &amp; Gourbault N. 1989. Desmodoridae from the Bay of Morlaix (Brittany) and the Southern Bight of the North Sea. Cahiers de Biologie Marine 30: 103 - 114." type="journal article" year="1989">Vincx &amp; Gourbault 1989</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC20B1539CBF8F7FA81F84D" blockId="6.[189,1399,1829,1961]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B1539CBF8F7FDDDF8DB" authority="(Cobb, 1914)" authorityName="Leduc &amp; Verschelde" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Cobb" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[189,554,1829,1855]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="septentrionalis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B1539CBF8F7FE70F8DB" box="[189,391,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">P. septentrionalis</emphasis>
(Cobb, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0DFFA27BFFC20B153B47F8F4FD45F8DB" box="[561,690,1829,1855]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(synonyms: 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B153A3EF8F7FB08F8DB" authority="(Cobb, 1914)" baseAuthorityName="Cobb" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[840,1279,1829,1856]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Spirinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153A3EF8F7FBABF8DB" box="[840,1116,1829,1856]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spirinia septentrionalis</emphasis>
(Cobb, 1914)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC20B153C41F8F7FDF6F886" authority="Cobb, 1914" authorityName="Cobb" authorityYear="1914" baseAuthorityName="Cobb" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Peranemea" family="Astasiidae" genus="Spira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Natomonadida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Euglenozoa" rank="species" species="septentrionalis">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC20B153C41F8F7FE9CF886" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Spira septentrionalis</emphasis>
Cobb, 1914
</taxonomicName>
). Main diagnostic characters: ‘‘From the anus the tail tapers for two-thirds of its length, then becomes cylindroid to the swollen terminus…’’ Drawings by 
<bibRefCitation id="4029BEE3FFC20B153D13F8BAFAFFF861" author="Wieser W." box="[1125,1288,1899,1925]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref11656" refString="Wieser W. 1954. Free-living nematodes II. Chromadoroidea. Lunds Universitets Arsskrift, N. F. Avd. 2 50 (16): 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1954">Wieser (1954</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 126) clearly show the amphids in the head region with only their posterior half within the body annulations,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC30B1439CBFEDBFD32FEA3" blockId="7.[189,1398,266,327]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
leaving the anterior half on the non-annulated head region. The tail is conico-cylindrical. Thus, this species is transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC30B143B39FEFFFD49FEA3" authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[591,702,302,327]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B143B39FEFFFD49FEA3" box="[591,702,302,327]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC30B1439CBFEA1FBF0FE4F" blockId="7.[189,1399,366,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC30B1439CBFEA1FDC8FE6C" authority="(Timm, 1962)" baseAuthorityName="Timm" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[189,575,366,393]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="striaticaudata">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B1439CBFEA1FE72FE6C" box="[189,389,366,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">P. striaticaudata</emphasis>
(Timm, 1962)
</taxonomicName>
. Tail long (11–17 abd) and slender with distinct annuli; thus it is transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC30B143817FE42FE27FE48" authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[353,464,403,428]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B143817FE42FE27FE48" box="[353,464,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Synonym: 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC30B143B10FE43FBF4FE4F" authority="Timm, 1962" authorityName="Timm" authorityYear="1962" box="[614,1027,401,428]" class="Chromadorea" family="Linhomoeidae" genus="Spirina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monhysterida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="striaticaudata">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B143B10FE43FC9EFE4F" box="[614,873,401,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Spirina striaticaudata</emphasis>
Timm, 1962
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC30B1439CBFE03FE53FE09" blockId="7.[189,420,466,493]" box="[189,420,466,493]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading id="7F4F747EFFC30B1439CBFE03FE53FE09" bold="true" box="[189,420,466,493]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B1439CBFE03FE53FE09" bold="true" box="[189,420,466,493]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Species inquirenda</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2407C312FFC30B1439CBFDD2FE23FD61" blockId="7.[189,1399,513,645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC30B1439CBFDD2FE46FDFF" box="[189,433,513,540]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="sabulicola">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B1439CBFDD2FE46FDFF" box="[189,433,513,540]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria sabulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Filipjev, 1918/1921) comb. nov. (synonym: 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC30B143A96FDD3FA99FDFF" authority="Filipjev, 1918" authorityName="Filipjev" authorityYear="1918" box="[992,1390,513,540]" class="Chromadorea" family="Linhomoeidae" genus="Spirina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monhysterida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="species" species="sabulicola">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B143A96FDD3FB4BFDFF" box="[992,1212,513,540]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Spirina sabulicola</emphasis>
Filipjev, 1918
</taxonomicName>
/ 1921). This species was described with a ‘long tail (length 4 × width)’ and hence should be transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="E3B8B891FFC30B143825FD98FE35FD86" authorityName="Wieser &amp; Hopper" authorityYear="1967" box="[339,450,585,610]" class="Adenophorea" family="Desmodoridae" genus="Perspiria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Desmodorida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B143825FD98FE35FD86" box="[339,450,585,610]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Perspiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, as the species was described based on only one female, it is regarded as a 
<emphasis id="16CC1F00FFC30B143987FDBDFE3AFD61" box="[241,461,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">species inquirenda</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
